					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'd always make sure that my programms could work fine on both PAL and NTSC. If your raster timing work in PAL and your VBLank timing works in NTSC, then normally the whole thing should work under both. The VBlank is longer in PAL, but the frame is shorter, and the CPU overall slower. Look <a href="http://nesdevwiki.org/wiki/NES_PPU" class="postlink">here</a> for more details.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
